  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2011-12-16",
    "date": "2012-01-31T20:51:39Z",
    "text": "Authorizes the award of a single Congressional Gold Medal to collectively honor the troops from the United States and the Philippines who defended Bataan, Philippines, and were subsequently prisoners of war, in recognition of their personal sacrifice and service to their country during World War II. Provides for the Medal's display at the Smithsonian Institution.\n\nExpresses the sense of Congress that the Medal should be made available for display elsewhere, particularly at locations associated with the prisoners of war at Bataan."
  },
